import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['start'] = pd.to_datetime(data['start'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x='start', data=data)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title("What is the distribution of monarchs by their reign start year?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['start'] = pd.to_datetime(data['start'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data['end'] = pd.to_datetime(data['end'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data['reign_length'] = (data['end'] - data['start']).dt.days / 365.25

    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(data=data, y='reign_length')
    plt.title("What is the average length of a monarch's reign?", wrap=True)

    avg_reign_length = np.mean(data['reign_length'])
    plt.axhline(avg_reign_length, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_reign_length:.2f} years')
    plt.legend()

    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    names = ' '.join(data['name'].tolist())
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=480, height=480, margin=0).generate(names)
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.title("What is the most common name among the monarchs?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['start'] = pd.to_datetime(data['start'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data['end'] = pd.to_datetime(data['end'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    commonwealth_counts = data['commonwealth'].value_counts()
    labels = ['Commonwealth' if x == 1 else 'Not Commonwealth' for x in commonwealth_counts.index]
    plt.pie(commonwealth_counts, labels=labels, autopct='%.2f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of monarchs by their affiliation with the Commonwealth?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['end'] = pd.to_datetime(data['end'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data['end_year'] = data['end'].dt.year
    year_counts = data['end_year'].value_counts().reset_index().rename(columns={'index': 'year', 'end_year': 'count'})
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='count', data=year_counts)
    
    ax = plt.gca()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of monarchs by their reign end year?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
